content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 1271.9 - Starting engines where exhaust blast may cause injury or damage prohibited

State Regulations

No jet or turbo-prop aircraft engines shall be started
while the aircraft is parked on the air terminal where exhaust blast may cause
injury to persons or do damage to property. Notes
